SIMPLE: irritant
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Irritant
<hw>Ir"ri*tant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>irritants</ets>, <ets>-antis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>irritare</ets>
to make null, fr. L. <ets>irritus</ets> void; pref. <ets>ir-</ets> not +
<ets>ratus</ets> established.]</ety> <fld>(Scots Law)</fld>
<def>Rendering null and void; conditionally invalidating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The states elected Harry, Duke of Anjou, for their king, with this
clause <qex>irritant</qex>; that, if he did violate any part of his
oath, the people should owe him no allegiance.</q>
<rj><qau>Hayward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Irritant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Irritant
<hw>Ir"ri*tant</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>irritans</ets>,
<ets>-antis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>irritare</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>irritant</ets>. See <er>Irritate</er> to excite.]</ety>
<def>Irritating; producing irritation or inflammation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Irritant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Irritant
<hw>Ir"ri*tant</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>irritant</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>That which irritates or excites.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physiol. & Med.)</fld> <def>Any agent by which
irritation is produced; <as>as, a chemical <ex>irritant</ex>; a
mechanical or electrical <ex>irritant</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Toxicology)</fld> <def>A poison that produces
inflammation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Counter irritant</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Counter</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Pure irritant</b></col>
<fld>(Toxicology)</fld>, <cd>a poison that produces inflammation without
any corrosive action upon the tissues.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Irritate</ent>⟦br⟧
